Two persons died and three others sustained injuries in a fatal motor accident at Munkawo Village in Birniwa local Government Area of Jigawa State. Spokesman of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, NSCDC, in the state, SC. Adamu Shehu confirmed the incident to DAILY POST. He said the incident happened on Tuesday afternoon along Birniwa and Malam-Madori road. Adamu explained that the accident occurred when a Sharon vehicle driver with registration number NSR894XA lost control and crushed a motorcycle. He said five people were involved in the accident out of which two died and the other three injured. Adamu said the injured victims were taken to Birniwa General Hospital for medical treatment while the corpses were deposited at the hospital mortuary. This is coming days after nine persons lost their lives in another accident in Birniwa Local Government Area of the state.